<p>of slacks &amp; cleaning up first class.  He did not get off, although for the work he did in getting ready he should have done.  A chap lucky enough to have new clothes &amp; who made the most of them, got off.</p>
<p>Since I had a plain home talk with Wainwright up the line he has been very affable with me, &amp; this incident of cleaning up for guard marked a turning point <strike>in his</strike> ( or what looks like one) in his army career.</p>
